  "text": "The Kubernetes API server admission webhook chain is implemented across multiple files in the kubernetes/kubernetes repository, primarily in the staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver directory. The architecture consists of several key layers:\n\n## Core Admission Chain\n\nThe foundational admission chain mechanism is in staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/chain.go, which implements `chainAdmissionHandler` - a slice of admission handlers that sequentially processes admission requests. The chain calls either `Admit()` for mutation or `Validate()` for validation on each handler that handles the given operation.\n\nAdmission handler types are defined in staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/interfaces.go, which specifies the `Interface`, `MutationInterface`, and `ValidationInterface` that webhook plugins must implement.\n\n## Webhook Plugin Infrastructure\n\nThe webhook plugins are built on a generic foundation:\n\n- **staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/generic/webhook.go** - The `Webhook` base class that provides common webhook infrastructure including configuration management, initialization, and dispatch orchestration.\n\n- **staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/generic/interfaces.go** - Defines the `Dispatcher` interface that webhook-specific implementations must satisfy, and the `Source` interface for retrieving webhook configurations.\n\n## Webhook Call Dispatch\n\nMutating and validating webhooks implement separate dispatchers:\n\n- **staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/mutating/dispatcher.go** - The `mutatingDispatcher` implements the `Dispatcher` interface and handles calling mutating webhooks. It manages webhook invocation ordering, re-invocation logic when webhooks mutate the object, and handles JSON patch responses by applying patches to the request object.\n\n- **staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/validating/dispatcher.go** - The `validatingDispatcher` handles validating webhooks. Unlike mutating webhooks, validating webhooks are called in parallel for performance optimization and cannot mutate the request object.\n\n## Webhook Plugins\n\n- **staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/mutating/plugin.go** - Implements the `Plugin` struct for mutating webhooks with an `Admit()` method that delegates to the generic webhook dispatcher.\n\n- **staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/validating/plugin.go** - Implements the `Plugin` struct for validating webhooks with a `Validate()` method that delegates to the generic webhook dispatcher.\n\n## Webhook Configuration Management\n\nWebhook configurations are managed by:\n\n- **staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/configuration/mutating_webhook_manager.go** - The `mutatingWebhookConfigurationManager` watches MutatingWebhookConfiguration resources and provides access to currently active mutating webhooks.\n\n- **staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/configuration/validating_webhook_manager.go** - The `validatingWebhookConfigurationManager` watches ValidatingWebhookConfiguration resources and provides access to currently active validating webhooks.\n\n## Admission Request/Response Handling\n\n- **staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/request/admissionreview.go** - Creates AdmissionReview objects to send to webhooks via `CreateAdmissionObjects()` and verifies webhook responses with `VerifyAdmissionResponse()`.\n\n## Supporting Infrastructure\n\n- **staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/accessors.go** - Webhook accessor types for unified access to mutating and validating webhooks.\n\n- **staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/initializer/initializer.go** - Initializes webhooks with required dependencies from the API server.\n\n- **staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/predicates/** - Implements matching logic for rules, namespaces, and objects to determine if a webhook should be invoked.\n\n- **staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/matchconditions/matcher.go** - Evaluates CEL-based match conditions for webhook invocation.\n\n- **staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/errors/statuserror.go** - Webhook-specific error handling and status conversion.\n\n- **staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/util/webhook/** - Utilities for webhook HTTP client management, authentication, error handling, and metrics.\n\n## KubeAPIServer Integration\n\n- **pkg/kubeapiserver/admission/config.go** - Configuration for initializing admission plugins in the Kubernetes API server.\n\n- **pkg/kubeapiserver/admission/initializer.go** - Kubeapiserver-specific initialization of admission webhooks.\n\n## Execution Flow\n\nWhen a request arrives at the API server, it flows through the admission chain. When it reaches webhook plugins:\n\n1. The generic `Webhook.Dispatch()` method retrieves active webhooks from the configuration manager.\n2. For each webhook, `ShouldCallHook()` determines if the webhook should be invoked based on rules, namespace selectors, and object selectors.\n3. If invocation is needed, the request is converted to an AdmissionReview object.\n4. The dispatcher calls the webhook via HTTP with the AdmissionReview.\n5. For mutating webhooks: patches are applied to the request object if provided; if a webhook mutates the object, other eligible mutating webhooks may be re-invoked.\n6. For validating webhooks: the response is verified; if validation fails, the request is rejected.\n7. Aggregated responses are collected and any errors result in request rejection."
